class.name: anywheresoftware.b4j.objects.StatusBarWrapper
class.comment: A bar that is usually added at the bottom of the form. It shows a label at the left side and a progress bar at the right side. You can add more nodes.

property.name: Progress
property.comment: Gets or sets the progress bar value. This is a value between 0 to 1.

property.name: RightItems
property.comment: Returns a List of the nodes at the right side. You can add nodes to this list.

property.name: LeftItems
property.comment: Returns a List of the nodes at the left side. You can add nodes to this list.

property.name: Text
property.comment: Gets or sets the default label text value.

class.name: anywheresoftware.b4j.objects.SeparatorWrapper
class.comment: A vertical separator. Can be used with StatusBar to separate nodes.

class.name: anywheresoftware.b4j.objects.SegmentedButtonWrapper
class.comment: A control that holds a set of toggle buttons.

property.name: SelectedItem
property.comment: Gets or sets the selected item. Will return an empty string if no item is selected.

property.name: DarkStyle
property.comment: Set to true to use dark style instead of the default style.

class.name: anywheresoftware.b4j.objects.RangeSliderWrapper
class.comment: A vertical or horizontal slider with two thumbs that allows the user to select a range. The range is defined between the low value and the high value.
class.event: ValueChange (LowValue As Double, HighValue As Double)

property.name: Vertical
property.comment: Gets or sets the slider orientation. The default value is False (horizontal).

property.name: ShowTickMarks
property.comment: Set to True to show tick marks.

property.name: HighValue
property.comment: Gets or sets the current high value.

property.name: MinValue
property.comment: Gets or sets the minimum value. The default value is 0.

property.name: SnapToTicks
property.comment: Set to True to make the thumbs snap to the nearest tick.

property.name: ShowTickLabels
property.comment: Set to true to show tick labels.

property.name: MinorTickCount
property.comment: Gets or sets the number of minor ticks between major ticks.

property.name: MaxValue
property.comment: Gets or sets the maximum value. The default value is 100.

property.name: MajorTickUnit
property.comment: Gets or sets the distance between major ticks. Default value is 25.

property.name: LowValue
property.comment: Gets or sets the current low value.

method.name: Set
method.comment: Sets the type instance that holds the data and a Map with the meta data that describes each of the fields.

method.name: CreateMeta
method.comment: Creates a PropertyMetaData object that describes a single property. Name - The text that will appear at the left side of the property. Category - The category that holds this property. Description - Longer text that appears when as the property tool tip.

property.name: SearchBoxVisible
property.comment: Gets or sets whether the search box is visible.

property.name: ModeSwitcherVisible
property.comment: Gets or sets whether the mode switcher is visible.

class.name: anywheresoftware.b4j.objects.PropertySheetWrapper.PropertyMetaData
class.comment: Meta-data describing a single property field.

method.name: SetChoices
method.comment: Limits the possible values. Only supported for strings and numbers types.

class.name: anywheresoftware.b4j.objects.ListSelectionViewWrapper
class.comment: A view that holds two lists (source and target) and allows the user to move items from one list to the other.

property.name: SourceTitle
property.comment: Gets or sets the source list title.

property.name: SourceItems
property.comment: Returns the source items. You can add string items to this list.

property.name: TargetTitle
property.comment: Gets or sets the target list title.

property.name: TargetItems
property.comment: Returns the target items. You can add string items to this list.

property.name: ShowOnHover
property.comment: Gets or sets whether the overlay expands when the mouse hovers over the inner node. Default value is True.

property.name: Text
property.comment: Gets or sets the overlay text.

property.name: InnerNode
property.comment: Gets or sets the inner node.

property.name: Text
property.comment: Gets or sets the text. Text between square brackets will be treated as a link.

method.name: RemoveDecorations
method.comment: Removes all decorations from the given node.

method.name: SetBackgroundColor
method.comment: Sets the control background color. ImageView, Canvas and WebView do not support this method.

method.name: DisableCssWarnings
method.comment: Disables Css warnings from appearing in the logs.

method.name: SetSize
method.comment: Sets the width and height of the node. This method will set the correct width and height properties based on the node type.

method.name: SetBackgroundImage
method.comment: Sets the control background image. ImageView, Canvas and WebView do not support this method.

method.name: ShowNotification2
method.comment: Similar to ShowNotification. If the Owner property is not null the message will appear inside the form.

method.name: ShowNotification3
method.comment: Similar to ShowNotification2. Position - The message position. The possible values are: TOP_LEFT, TOP_CENTER, TOP_RIGHT, CENTER_LEFT, CENTER, CENTER_RIGHT, BOTTOM_LEFT, BOTTOM_CENTER and BOTTOM_RIGHT. DurationMs - Message duration in milliseconds.

method.name: ShowNotification
method.comment: Shows a notification message in the bottom right corner of the main screen. The message will disappear after 5 seconds. Title - Message title. Text - Message Text. Icon - One of the ICON constants.

method.name: AddDecoration
method.comment: Adds a decoration image to the node. Position - Decoration position. The possible values are: TOP_LEFT, TOP_CENTER, TOP_RIGHT, CENTER_LEFT, CENTER, CENTER_RIGHT, BOTTOM_LEFT, BOTTOM_CENTER and BOTTOM_RIGHT. OffsetX / OffsetY - Offset from the corner measured in pixels.

class.name: anywheresoftware.b4j.objects.CheckComboBoxWrapper
class.comment: A ComboBox control. Each item is made of a string and check box. The CheckedChange event happens whenever one of the items is checked or unchecked (whether by the user or by code).

method.name: SetChecked
method.comment: Sets the checked state of the item at the given index.

method.name: GetCheckedIndices
method.comment: Returns a list with the indices of the checked items.

method.name: IsChecked
method.comment: Returns true if the item at the given index is checked.

property.name: Items
property.comment: Returns a List with the items. You can add strings to this list.

class.name: anywheresoftware.b4j.objects.BreadCrumbBarWrapper
class.comment: A bar with one or more segments that allow the user to go back to a previous state.

method.name: GetItems
method.comment: Returns a list with the current items.

property.name: AutoNavigationEnabled
property.comment: Gets or sets whether the items will collapse automatically when clicked. Default value is true.

property.name: SelectedValue
property.comment: Returns the value of the right most item.
